abstract: MONTICELLO, N.Y., June 30.--Typhus fever is prevalent among cattle in portions or Sullivan County. Nicholas Dauch, a farmer near Mountaindale, has lost five animals within 24 hours from the disease. Sylvester Crossman, a neighbor of Dauch, has lost four cows. The symptoms resemble bloody murrain. There is a loss of appetite, great thirst and diarrhea, followed quickly by spasms and paralysis.
